Kirsten Dawn Madison of Florida has been nominated to be an Assistant Secretary of State for International Narcotics and Law Enforcement Affairs. She has extensive experience in foreign and national security policy, having worked for various organizations including the American Enterprise Institute, the U.S. Senate Committee on Foreign Relations, and the U.S. Coast Guard. Ms. Madison has also run programs to support the State Department's Bureau of International Narcotics and Law Enforcement Affairs. She holds a M.Sc. from the London School of Economics and Political Science and a B.A. from Goucher College.